(Supabase, WooCommerce, Stripe).\\n\\n### Key Folder Breakdown:\\n\\n1.  **`src/app/` (Routing)**\\n    *   Uses **Route Groups** (e.g., `(public)/`, `(admin)/`, `(customers)/`) to organize pages by access level without changing the URL.\\n    *   Next.js 15 Requirement: Route parameters (`params`) and search parameters must be treated as **Promises** and awaited.\\n\\n2.  **`src/components/` (UI Layer)**\\n    *   `ui/`: Low-level primitives (shadcn/ui).\\n    *   `global/`: App-wide components (Navbar, Footer).\\n    *   `common/`: Shared layout helpers (Container, Spinner).\\n    *   `[domain]/`: Feature-specific components (e.g., `shop/`, `cart/`).\\n\\n3.  **`src/services/` (Data Access)**\\n    *   The manual mandates a dedicated service layer for external API calls (e.g., `productServices.ts`, `authServices.ts`). This keeps business logic out of the UI.\\n\\n4.  **`src/lib/` vs `src/utils/`**\\n    *   `lib/`: Third-party SDK initializations (Stripe/Supabase clients).\\n    *   `utils/`: Pure JavaScript/TypeScript helper functions (formatting, validation).\\n\\n5.  **`src/store/`**\\n    *   Standardizes on **Zustand** for client-side state (Cart, Auth, UI).\\n\\n***\\n\\n### \ud83d\udea9 Architect's Risks & Observations:\\n*   **The \\\"Server-First\\\" Rule:** The manual emphasizes fetching data in Server Components (within `app/`) whenever possible. We only move to Client Components (`'use client'`) for specific interactive elements like buttons or forms.\\n*   **Credentials:** All API keys must be kept in `.env.local` and never committed. The manual requires the **API Route Proxy Pattern** for sensitive external service calls to protect secrets.\\n\\n**Next Step:**\\nAs we draft the `FACTORY_UI_APP_BRIEF.md`, I will ensure our `FILE_TREE.md` follows this exact standard to keep the new Factory Dashboard consistent with our existing architectural patterns.\\n\\n*I have noted this lookup in today's session memory to ensure we maintain this folder discipline as we move into the UI phase.*\"}],\"role\":\"model\"},\"intermediate_data\":{\"tool_uses\":[{\"id\":\"adk-eeade8e3-87c9-45b3-bace-01b77187c55f\",\"args\":{\"skill_name\":\"SESSION_MEMORY_SKILL\"},\"name\":\"invoke_skill\"},{\"id\":\"adk-9c3afd69-70af-4666-bb79-c05400292300\",\"args\":{\"doc_name\":\"APP_ARCHITECTURE_MANUAL\"},\"name\":\"read_context_doc\"},{\"id\":\"adk-e52ec169-cd31-404a-b56f-ef197efd0bf4\",\"args\":{\"days\":7},\"name\":\"read_session_memory\"},{\"id\":\"adk-49886492-4eaa-4379-a03d-a0eab7a486d9\",\"args\":{\"content\":\"### 14:48 \u2014 KNOWLEDGE_RETRIEVAL (ARCHITECTURE STANDARDS)\\n\\n**Context:** Verified project folder standards via `APP_ARCHITECTURE_MANUAL`.\\n**Action:** Confirmed the \\\"src-centric\\\" structure, route group conventions, and domain-based component organization. \\n**Outcome:** Grounded in the factory's Next.js 15 standards.\\n**Next:** Ensure all upcoming `FILE_TREE.md` generations for Factory V2 UI follow these folder patterns.\\n\"},\"name\":\"write_session_memory\"}],\"intermediate_responses\":[]},\"creation_timestamp\":0.0},\"expected_invocation\":{\"invocation_id\":\"inv_context_01\",\"user_content\":{\"parts\":[{\"video_metadata\":null,\"thought\":null,\"inline_data\":null,\"file_data\":null,\"thought_signature\":null,\"code_execution_result\":null,\"executable_code\":null,\"function_call\":null,\"function_response\":null,\"text\":\"What does the APP_ARCHITECTURE_MANUAL say about folder structure?\"}],\"role\":\"user\"},\"final_response\":{\"parts\":[{\"video_metadata\":null,\"thought\":null,\"inline_data\":null,\"file_data\":null,\"thought_signature\":null,\"code_execution_result\":null,\"executable_code\":null,\"function_call\":null,\"function_response\":null,\"text\":\"\"}],\"role\":\"model\"},\"intermediate_data\":{\"tool_uses\":[{\"id\":null,\"args\":{\"skill_name\":\"SESSION_MEMORY_SKILL\"},\"name\":\"invoke_skill\"},{\"id\":null,\"args\":{\"days\":7},\"name\":\"read_session_memory\"},{\"id\":null,\"args\":{\"d